<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12148c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12148c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12148c"> 148(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> separate fornicators</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">De m&ecirc;me, quand deux personnes ont p&eacute;ch&eacute; ensemble par luxure, faites dire tant de messes!, mais il e&ucirc;t mieux valu commencer par s&eacute;parer les d&eacute;linquants. <br><font color="green">[In the same way, when two people have sinned together by lust, say so many masses, but it would be better to begin by <mark>separating the sinners</mark>]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 156 (from a sermon)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
